metadata.metaValue: Check match one character at a time

If the expression ends with a `*` and is shorter than the name to match against, it will append some `*` until expression length is the same.
 
Example: 
```
Name:       ABCDEF
Expression: AB*
Output:     AB****
```
A match is when the name character is the same than the expression char or when the expression char is `*`
Return false early if expression longer than name

If the expression starts with a `*` and is shorter than the name to match against, it will prepend some `*` until expression length is the same.
 
Example: 
```
Name:       ABCDEF
Expression: *EF
Output:     ****EF
```
